</header><div class="entry-content" itemprop="text"><p><strong>Due Date</strong><br />
Your ZOT Account reflects charges billed to you, as well as credits and payments made to the account.  <strong>Generally, balances are due by the 15th of every month</strong>.  If the 15th falls on a weekend or holiday, your balance will be due on the next business day.  </p>
<p>To view your ZOT Account Online, go to <a href="https://zotaccount.uci.edu" title="zot account"><strong>https://zotaccount.uci.edu</strong></a><br />
Before you may use your ZOT Account Online it is imperative that you:</p>
<ul>
<li>activate your UCInetID; and</li>
<li>review your messages in your UCI mailbox; and</li>
<li>maintain your mailbox and prevent it from getting full. (If your mailbox is full, important messages, such as ZOTBills, cannot be delivered.)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>You may pay your ZOT Account</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>in person by cash or check at the Central Cashier.</li>
<li>by mail to the Central Cashier.</li>
<li>with an electronic check through your ZOT Account</li>
</ul>
<p><em>See more about <a href="https://fs.uci.edu/payments/general-information-about-payments/" title="General Information About Payments">Payments</a>.</em></p>
<p>You may pay for Registration Fees using the <strong><a href="https://fs.uci.edu/billing/pace-payment-plan-for-registration-fees/" title="PACE Payment Plan for Registration Fees">PACE</a></strong> payment plan through your Zot Account.<br />
<em>See more about the <a href="https://fs.uci.edu/billing/pace-payment-plan-for-registration-fees/" title="PACE Payment Plan for Registration Fees">PACE payment plan</a>.</em></p>
<p><strong>Amount Due / Account Balance</strong><br />
There are also instances where a charge may be placed on your account with a future due date, such as Registration Fees or Housing Charges.  This is likely the explanation if your &#8220;Amount Due&#8221; is less than your &#8220;Account Balance&#8221;.  </p>
<p><strong>Late Fees &amp; Financial Holds</strong><br />
Your ZOT Account will incur late fees if the amount due or balance is not paid by the due date.  A Financial Hold will also be placed on your account if a balance is not paid.  Financial Holds can result in a denial of services including registration for future enrollment, processing of transcript requests, and issuance of your diploma.  Holds that remain on your record at the fee payment deadline can result in your classes being dropped.</p>
<p><strong>Collection Accounts</strong><br />
Unpaid balances may be written off and referred to an outside agency for collections.</p>
<p>If you have any questions regarding your ZOT Account, please contact Campus Billing at cbs@uci.edu or call 949 UCI BILL (949.824.2455).</p>
<table cellpadding="15">
<tr>
<td width="300" valign="top"><strong>Types of Charges</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Registration Fees</li>
<li>Housing Charges and/or Monthly Rent</li>
<li>Lab Fees</li>
<li>LARC Bills</li>
<li>eTech (Electronic Technology Fees)</li>
<li>Late Fees</li>
<li>Financial Aid Adjustments</li>
<li>PACE Monthly Installments</li>
<li>PACE Participation Fee</li>
<li>Other miscellaneous charges</li>
</ul>
</td>
<td valign="top"><strong>Types of Credits</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Payments</li>
<li>Financial Aid Funds</li>
<li>PACE Payment Plan</li>
<li>Health Insurance Waivers</li>
<li>Miscellaneous Fee Waivers</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Other Adjustments</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Write Off to collections</li>
<li>Overpayment Refunds</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
